[3
Date: Sat, 28 Aug 1999 13:19:54 -0500
From: "Dr. Norman Ronald" <n-ronald@TVMDL.TAMU.EDU>

The greatest single menace of hurricane Bret may be an upsurge in the number
of cases of dengue north of the Rio Grande River. Texans were very thankful
that the hurricane made landfall in Kennedy County, which is the least
populated county on the Gulf Coast. However, the rains generated from
Hurricane Bret fell in the area where dengue cases have occurred.
